description.plain:
Lathan Moses Stanley Echols (b. January 25, 2002), better known by his stage name Lil Mosey, is a rapper from Seattle, Washington.

He first garnered buzz via Sound Cloud and Instagram with a string of singles. He first started to make noise with his song “Pull Up,” but the track’s success was soon eclipsed by “Noticed.” The popularity of these songs among others landed him a spot as an opener on his label-mate Juice WRLD’s WRLD Domination tour, and a record deal with Interscope in 2018.

In October 2018, Mosey’s first commercial mixtape Northsbest was released (not to be confused with his 2017 mixtape NorthsBest, which shares the same name).

November 2019 saw the release of his debut studio album, Certified Hitmaker. The album was then re-released the following February after the long-awaited release of “Blueberry Faygo,” which would go on to become Mosey’s first Billboard top 10 hit. The 20-track deluxe, Certified Hitmaker (AVA Leak), released in August 2020.

Mosey claims to be inspired by Philly rapper Meek Mill, and that one can hear the influence of OVO artist Drake’s sound in his music.

songs.title: Blueberry Faygo

description.plain:
“Blueberry Faygo” was expected to be the first single from Seattle rapper Lil Mosey in advance of his upcoming project, The Land of Make Believe. It was later added onto Mosey’s debut album, Certified Hitmaker, near the end of February 2020.

The song’s title is a reference to a flavor of Faygo, a soft drink company commonly referenced in hip-hop culture in relation to drug use, specifically, the abuse of lean and codeine.

While the song was never officially previewed by Mosey, it suffered a partial leak on June 5, 2019. In the months before the song officially released, the leak gained traction thanks to TikTok, and uploads of the leak saw millions of views across multiple platforms. However, the officially-released version of the track featured a new second verse which had only been briefly previewed by the verse’s recording studio.

songs.title: Noticed

description.plain:
Originally released in 2017, the remix of “Noticed” was released in July 2018 accompanied by a video directed by Cole Bennett, which subsequently racked up over 200 million views.

In this single Lil Mosey talks about how people changed because of his fame – but this doesn’t escape his attention. He also covers other familiar topics, such as getting money and taking drugs.

songs.title: Kamikaze

description.plain:
Lil Mosey’s first track, “Kamikaze”,  off of his debut studio album “Northsbest” has been positioned to become a hit from the start. “Kamikaze” was produced by Kid Culture & Royce David. Mosey most likely insinuates how him and his friends are ready for anything.

This track is his second major studio hit since “Noticed”. Both of these songs received a lot of attention with their Cole Bennett-directed music video.
